Citation.sTitle: Enthalpies of solution of L-phenylalanine in aqueous solution of amides at 298.15 K.
Citation.sAbstract: The enthalpies of solution have been determined for L-phenylalanine in aqueous solutions of formamide, N-methylformamide, N, Ndimethylformamide and N, N-dimethylacetamide. The measurements were made at 298.15 K and mole fraction of amide x2 = (0 to 0.35) on the precise isothermic calorimeter. The results obtained have been used to calculate the standard enthalpies of solution and transfer of L-phenylalanine from a water into mixtures as well as the enthalpy coefficients of pairwise interaction (hxy) of the solute with amide in aqueous media. It is established the interrelation between enthalpy characteristics of dissolution (transfer) of L-phenylalanine and the composition of (water+amide) binary mixtures. Contributions of the amides properties (molar volume, dipolarity/polarizability, acidity and basicity) to the energy of pairwise interactions have been estimated quantitatively with assistance of a modified Kamlet-Taft equation
Citation.sKeyword: amino acid, water, amides, enthalpy of solution,
